                "img": "https://arxiv.org/html/2605.15726/2605.15726v1/x2.png",
                "caption": "Figure 2:Overview of the NudgeRL learning mechanism.(a) Inter-Intra Group Advantage:Demonstrates credit assignment that emphasizes reliable contexts (i.e.,λ∈(1,2]\\lambda\\in(1,2]). A successful rollout from a consistently high-reward context (Strategy B) receives a larger positive advantage than a rare success from a low-reward context (Strategy A).(b) Self-distillation:Illustrates bridging the train-test gap. High-quality trajectories discovered via context-conditioned exploration (Q+BQ+B) are distilled back into the base policy (QQ) usingℒDistill\\mathcal{L}_{\\text{Distill}}, allowing the model to internalize effective reasoning modes for context-free inference.",
